.Dd $Mdocdate: December 29 2019 $
.Dt CHGRP 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm chgrp
.Nd change the file group ownership
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl h
.Op Fl R Op Fl H | L | P
.Ar group
.Ar
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility sets the group id of each
.Ar file
to the specified
.Ar group
id.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl H
Dereference symbolic links on command line.
.It Fl h
Modify links instead of following them.
.It Fl L
Dereference all symbolic links.
.It Fl P
Preserve symbolic links.
.It Fl R
Descend recursively through its directories arguments.
.El
.Pp
The default is as if the
.Fl P
option had been specified.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr chmod 1 ,
.Xr chown 1
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Nm
utility is compliant with the
.St -p1003.1-2017
specification.
